izide in humans." Diabetes Care 10 (1987): 683-6[8] Barnett AH, Spiliopoulos AJ, Pyke DA, et al "Metabolic studies in chlorpropamide-alcohol flush positive and negative type 2 (non-insulin dependent) diabetic patients with and without retinopathy." Diabetologia 24 (1983): 213-5[9] Cerner Multum, Inc. "UK Summary of Product Characteristics." O 0[10] "Product Information. Diabeta (glyburide)." Hoechst Marion-Roussel Inc, Kansas City, MO.[11] Jerntorp P, Almer LO, Holin H, et al "Plasma chlorpropamide: a critical factor in chlorpropamide-alcohol flush." Eur J Clin Pharmacol 24 (1983): 237-42[12] Wohlt PD, Zheng L, Gunderson S, Balzar SA, Johnson BD, Fish JT "Recommendations for the use of medications with continuous enteral nutrition." Am J Health Syst Pharm 66 (2009): 1438-67[13] "Product Information. VFEND (voriconazole)." Pfizer U.S. Pharmaceuticals, New York, NY.', 1767369485);
